definition: one of the characters used in kwukyel, an ancient Korean writing system
lit. to kill the chicken to get the eggs (idiom)/fig. to kill the goose that lays the golden eggs
lit. to strike a stone with egg (idiom); to attempt the impossible/to invite disaster by overreaching oneself
precarious as pile of eggs (idiom); ready to fall and break at any moment/in a dangerous state

sentences.english: The fringelike fimbriae transport ovulated eggs from the ovarian surface to the infundibulum.
sentences.chinese: 花边状的伞将排出的卵，从卵巢表面运送到漏斗。

sentences.english: Blastula and gastrulae arrived 1 and 4 d after fertilization.
sentences.chinese: 在卵受精后第1天和第4天分别到达囊胚期和原肠期。

sentences.english: The dead cysts in the collection of Barkol Lake were mainly emerged in spring.
sentences.chinese: 巴里坤湖成品卤虫卵中的死卵主要产生在春季。

sentences.english: the eggs are collected before they divide and are injected with the foreign genetic material.
sentences.chinese: 将这些卵收集起来，在其卵裂前注入外来基因物质。

sentences.english: This made no sense. All the eggs are fertilized already.
sentences.chinese: 这可说不通，因为所有的卵都已经受精了。

sentences.english: Rain and cool temperature will kill many of the eggs the grasshoppers are laying today.
sentences.chinese: 雨水和冷凉的气温能破坏蝗虫现在产下的许多卵。

sentences.english: Granulosa cell apoptosis was detected by agarose gel electrophoresis.
sentences.chinese: 用琼脂糖凝胶电泳检测两类卵的颗粒细胞凋亡。

sentences.english: Natural survival rate of eggs and the various instar larvae in different years were also investigated.
sentences.chinese: 并观察了不同年份棉铃虫卵和各龄幼虫的自然存活率。

sentences.english: A big bunch of bullfrog eggs float in the pond.
sentences.chinese: 一大堆牛蛙的卵在池塘上。

sentences.english: At the right is a probe patent foramen ovale in an adult.
sentences.chinese: 右为成年人卵圆孔未闭的探查。

sentences.english: The knots, it turns out, aren't getting enough horseshoe crab eggs to eat.
sentences.chinese: 事实证明，红腹滨鹬没有吃到足够的马蹄蟹卵。

sentences.english: I believe these are eggs (ova) of the Enterobius vermicularis, a pinworm, that often habits in perianal areas.
sentences.chinese: 我相信这是蛲虫卵，一个蛲虫，往往习惯在周围区域。

sentences.english: In its lifetime, a female ladybug will lay as many as 2, 000 eggs.
sentences.chinese: 在雌性瓢虫的一生中将产下多达2000枚的卵。

sentences.english: Zeus stood up to shake off the dung pellet, and the eggs were thrown to the ground without his thinking.
sentences.chinese: 宙斯站起身来抖落粪蛋，没留神把鹰卵也抖掉了。

sentences.english: The heat of the sun hatches turtles' eggs.
sentences.chinese: 太阳的热能将陆龟的卵孵出小龟。

sentences.english: Conclusion The hatch phase of field ground is…
sentences.chinese: 结论养殖基地更利于蛤蚧卵的孵化。

definition: lower form of animal life, including insects, insect larvae, worms and similar creatures/CL:條|条[tiao2],隻|只[zhi1]/(fig.) person with a particular undesirable characteristic
the young (unborn or newborn) of an animal/larva
imago (adult, sexually mature insect, the final stage of its development)
